    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Governing for a Greener World</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sophie Glass letter on Thomas L Friedman's March 27 column says cost of America's exploitation of energy resources and its careless use of SUV's and coal-fired power plants will be borne by future generations</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas L. Friedman wonders how future historians will explain President Bush's negligence in regard to the global energy crisis.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas L. Friedman wonders how future historians will explain President Bush's negligence in regard to the global energy crisis.</p>
        <p>I wonder how our grandchildren will forgive our exploitation of resources and our careless use of S.U.V.'s and coal-fired power plants. If the current administration chooses to ignore the energy crisis, it is our duty to reduce our personal reliance on fossil fuels.</p>
        <p>Sophie Glass  Larchmont, N.Y., March 27, 2005</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
